title.narrative: Central government expenditure covered through IFMIS
The budget execution rate is kept above 90% (excluding donor-funded projects)
Publication of budget execution reports on the MoFEA website after the reporting end period
GDP data regularly & publicly made available
Backlog in the reconciliation of government bank accounts held at the CBG reduced
Interface between Debt management system (CSCRMS) and IFMIS is operational to automate the preparation of debt projections and the execution and reporting of debt payments, respectively.

actual.value: 7 SOE's special purpose audits have been completed

title.narrative: Donor funds included under the IFMIS module (percentage of total donor funds)
Ghost workers eliminated (percentage of the total population of ghost workers identified)
Fully operational IFMIS at the government sites
HR module integrated into the IFMIS
IFMIS EFT module interfaced with the CBG systems
Reports posted on the GBoS website (including Census 2013, IHS 2015/2016, GBoS Annual Statistical Abstract, and Poverty Profile Report)

target.value: GBoS Annual Statistical Abstract and Poverty Profile Report

actual.value: IHS 2015/2016 and GBoS Annual Statistical Abstract is posted on the website.
